The base game is nicely paced for the first two acts, but the game gets a bit easier after. Upgrading money speed followed by money max, and spamming speed duck and ninja duck makes the rest of the game a breeze. Still a very fun game, with nice cartoony graphics and I quite enjoyed the jokes that were added in here and there. Also, ducks. Quacky Duck on the other hand is probably the worst Flappy Bird clone I have ever played. After grinding it to get the score of 50 for the achievement, I can say a lot of it depends on the RNG of the pipes. The jump for each tap is too high, especially for the duck's size and you're often left resorting to diving low and hitting frame perfect taps to avoid the bottom pipes in order to avoid going too high and hitting the top pipes. It seems like poor design in an effort to create artificial difficulty.

All in all a very fun game that deserves a longer sequel. I had plenty of fun with this gem, and although I hate to say this, I had one major issue concerning the difficulty curve. The first issue was the first stage boss at the last level. That crane is wickedly overpowered. It would be fine if it stayed in place, and the gimmick is it flings my birds into nonexistence, but it spawn kills my ducks and then pumps troops out. A little too hard for when you only have unlocked 4-5 birds so far.   This crane makes the other bosses look like jokes. Especially the pirate boss. Just farm up the money and send the doom invasion.  The last point for a sequel should be a form of upgrades for each duck respectively. Sure spend some duck bucks to unlock the assortment, but there should also be upgrades for each individual one as well as your base/productivity. Your base should definitely get upgrades to have defenses installed, and also to have more slots to put different ducks in.   All in all this game was a fantastic, brief trip. I finished it in about 2 hours give or take. Only once did I get stuck on that crane for 30 minutes but the rest was not overbearing in difficulty.

I am so sad that this awesome game is not doing well, this is not your fault it's android's fault. I wanted to buy this game, but I live in India and my bank SBI (State Bank of India) the largest bank in India is not compatible with Play Store (Which means no support for my, credit or debit card on Play Store). Please move on from this damned mobile platform to the Nintendo Switch (I will buy your game their). A lot of players realizing that there are no good games for the mobile platform has actually moved on to the Switch (hence it's success). But there are good games in Android, but it's too little too late and gamers (real gamers who want to game on the go) have already given it a pass. Do you remember when the Vita came out, people didn't buy it, because it was 2011 - 12 and people thought the big day for mobile gaming is here (hence Vita flopped so bad), but fast forward to 2017 and people matured and understand now that the big day will never come (hence the success of switch). Sorry about the rambling but my brother was a paid game developer for mobile, and he realized it too late. Real gamers have already given mobile gaming a pass, it's high time you do so too. I remember a time when mobile gaming was a thing, and we used to discuss it in our friends circle, now I get teased for choosing X box over ps4, no one talks about mobile gaming anymore (except 15 year olds, because their parent won't give them console, fearing it will hurt their studies). Please, you can produce crappy free to play here and probably get high ratings, or just follow your passion and make really good games that people will buy for the Nintendo Switch or one of the consoles. Sell it for 5 or 10 bucks there and I promise people will buy it.
